n ein Modell, welches an den Denkvoraussetzungen der Antike selbst gebildet wurde. Die griechisch-römischen und mediterranen Religionen und Philosophien - also auch das hellenistische Judentum und das Christentum - orientierten sich an den Modellen von Patronat und Loyalität. Das Verständnis der antiken Konversion muss also hier ansetzen. In diesem Zusammenhang wird auch die "Bekehrung" des Paulus neu gedeutet.  aThis monograph challenges the dominant psychological assumptions that attend modern treatments of ancient conversion and offers in its place a model based on categories the ancients themselves used: patronage and loyalty.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aConversionxChristianity. 0aConversion. 0aPatron and clientzGreece. 0aPatron and clientzRome. 4aKonversion (Religion). 4aPatronage. 4aPaulus (Apostel). 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / New Testament.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023854908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-DITION 2: BEST OF THEOLOGY TITLES IN ENGLISHz9783110305630oZDB-23-DBL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-DITION 2: BEST OF THEOLOGYz9783110305654oZDB-23-DBK0 cprintz978311018265140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311091560040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110915600423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110915600/original  a978-3-11-023854-9  DGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0 